  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National regulations:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key compliance measures:\n- Customer identification procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Enhanced due diligence for high-risk transactions\n- Record-keeping requirements\n\n4. Enforcement mechanisms:\n- Criminal penalties\n- Financial sanctions\n- Asset seizure\n- Prosecution of individuals and organizations\n\n5. Global cooperation:\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Cross-border investigative efforts\n- Coordinated legal actions against money laundering networks\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes by establishing standardized regulations and enforcement mechanisms.",
